А так я ставлю Bioshock Infinite 10 огребаний Букера из 10

Good:
- Complex and original story;
- Colorful, memorable characters;
- Top notch style, recreating a late 19th century city in a floating utopia;
- Tiny details that breathe life into the world;
- Pumped-up combat sets, plenty of ways to defeat your enemies with combinations of vigors and weapons, sometimes the environment too;
- Music always fits the moment and the era;

Bad:
- Vigors lack variety, so do weapons;
- Plot holes, fortunately not too noticeable;
- Combat can get monotonous at times;
- The sky-rail system is underdeveloped;

Conclusion: must-buy, despite its flaws and it being different in tone and atmosphere from the other Bioshock games, Infinity is worth experiencing.
